Name: MLB Walkout Songs
Description: Imagine walking out to a 60k+ crowd at Kauffman Stadium during the world series (Kauffman only holds 37k). What would your walkout anthem be? Feel free to specify the 10 seconds that would play if needed but it should be obvious.

Name: Cancelled Artists
Description: These songs must be by someone who society has collectively decided to shun. You know them when you see them. Their songs still bang though.

Name: Non-English Song
Description: Let's see if anyone other than Zach and James listens to worldwide music. This track must have lyrics that are primarily in a language other than English (songs with no lyrics aren't eligible and some english is okay).

Name: Modern Folklore
Description: Songs from the last 50ish years that tell a story. These tales should feel like an oral history, no Nancy Reagan. Folklore can be tales, myths, legends, proverbs… anything of that nature.

Name: Obscure Artists
Description: Time to show off that niche artist you love. Pick a song by an artist with <250k monthly listeners on Spotify.

Name: Free Round!
Description: Let's take a break mid-season and relax with an open prompt. Any song you want to show off, king.

Name: DJ spin that (new) shit
Description: Think you got a pulse on music? Then prove it by with a song that was released within 60 days of the round submission deadline this week. Let's not have a repeat of last season where we submit singles that came out prior to an album (cough, cough). Add the date your song was ORIGINALLY released in the comment.

Name: Simp Anthems
Description: These songs go a step farther than putting your partner first. The individuals who wrote them are down horrendous; have some self-respect!

Name: Boys will be Girls, Girls will be Boys
Description: That dude sounds like a lady…? Submit your best cover song that someone of the opposite gender of the original sings. MAKE SURE that you actually reference the original song and artist in your comment for validation when voting. DO YOUR RESEARCH ON THE ORIGINAL ARTIST SLOOTS!

Name: Songs used in films
Description: This one's for all the kino maxxing context kings in chat. A good song placement in a film can seriously elevate the vibes, making those epic moments all the more epic, those intimate moments all the more special. No songs made for the movie allowed- it takes a different skill to find the perfect song vs compose the perfect song. Include a clip of the scene in which your song appears in the comment so that people have something to base votes on.
